Auto Emailer - Usage Guide

This guide explains how to use the Auto Emailer project.

1. SETUP

Make sure you have Python 3.8 or above installed.

Clone or download this repository.

Open the folder in VS Code or any text editor.

2. INSTALL REQUIREMENTS

Run this command in the terminal (inside the project folder):

pip install -r requirements.txt

3. CONFIGURE EMAIL SETTINGS

Copy the file config_example.env and rename it as .env

Open .env and fill in your details:

SMTP_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
SMTP_PORT=587
EMAIL_ADDRESS=your.email@gmail.com
EMAIL_PASSWORD=your_app_password
TO_ADDRESS=recipient@example.com


‚ö†Ô∏è Note:
For Gmail, enable 2FA (Two Factor Authentication) and use an App Password ‚Äî not your normal password.

4. RUN THE SCRIPT

Use this command to run the script:

python main.py


You will be asked to enter:

Subject

Body

Recipient(s)

Attachment path (optional)

5. WHAT HAPPENS

The script reads your .env credentials.

Sends an email with the given subject and body.

If attachment is provided, it adds that file to the email.

You‚Äôll see a success message once it‚Äôs sent.

6. SECURITY TIPS

‚ùå Never upload .env to GitHub.

üîí Keep your credentials safe.

ü™™ Use App Passwords for email accounts.

7. TROUBLESHOOTING
Problem	Possible Fix
‚ùå SMTPAuthenticationError	Check your email or App Password
‚ùå FileNotFoundError	Check your attachment file path
